The Lagos State government on Wednesday confirmed the death of a COVID-19 patient in the state. Prof. Akin Abayomi, Commissioner of Health in the state disclosed that the deceased was a 66-year-old Briton who recently returned from India. In a series of tweets, Abayomi wrote on his official Twitter page: “Lagos recorded another COVID-19 related death; a 66-year-old Briton who travelled from India via Dubai to Lagos on 17th of March 2020. “Let’s stay home and stay safe to stop the spread of COVID-19 infection for a greater Lagos.” DAILY POST recalls that Lagos had last week confirmed their first COVID-19 related death. Meanwhile, the total number of COVID-19 cases in Nigeria is 254, according to NCDC. 